From ec6231e3d206eeed4d83f671d02e94122ed2ed27 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?Lo=C3=AFc=20Sang?= <loic.sang@6wind.com>
Date: Mon, 25 Aug 2025 09:48:28 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 3/9] bgpd: add sid allocation for unicast in the default vrf
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add "sid export <auto|index|explicit> [route-map]" command for unicast
in the default vrf. This will allocate a sid for the default vrf,
similar to 6b99a6c1510f ("lib: Attach uDT* SIDs for default VRF to `sr0`
instead of loopback"), due to a Linux limitation, main table and "sr0"
interface should be created to successfully install DT rule.

It will be used in the next commit to send updates with the srv6
attribute over unicast

Signed-off-by: Loïc Sang <loic.sang@6wind.com>
---
